perpetuated in a new form the Modernist "death of the author." In interpreting this symbolic demise, he shows how the official culture of the 1930s can be seen as a perverted realization of modernism's unrealizable project. An insightful and challenging interpretation of the era, Automatic for the Masses will be required reading for those interested in understanding early Soviet culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 16. Mai 2019) 0aModernism (Aesthetics)zSoviet Union. 0aModernism (Art)zSoviet Union. 0aSocialist realism in artzSoviet Union. 0aSocialist realism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Eastern (see also Russian & Former Soviet Union).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2015z9783110438673oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUTP eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2015z978311066769108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Pilot 2014-2015z978311060681208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Pilot 2014-2019z978311065878108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press eBook Package 2014-2015z978311049093040uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/9781442616936423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442616936.jpg  a978-3-11-049093-0  University of Toronto Press eBook Package 2014-2015  a978-3-11-060681-2  University of Toronto Press Pilot 2014-2015  a978-3-11-065878-1  University of Toronto Press Pilot 2014-2019b2019  a978-3-11-066769-1  UTP eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  